    <prp:code/>
    <prp:abstract>We propose  2.5 hour ALMA  observations of CO  J=1-0 to
characterize the  giant molecular clouds (GMCs) of  an extremely metal
poor  galaxy,   which  will  offer  crucial   insights  into  physical
conditions   of   interstellar    medium   of   the   first-generation
galaxies. With the proposed data, we will (1) probe the GMC properties
characterized  by  the  CO  line profiles  including  sizes,  velocity
dispersions and luminosities; and (2) measure the CO-to-H_2 factor
by  combining dust  measurements  from our  deep  Herschel data.   The
proposed  observation will  be a  great  advance in  studying ISMs  of
extremely low metallicity, only capable by ALMA.
 </prp:abstract>
